power_of_play_messages.msg: Time for some fun! 🤸🏾 Let's play together!
Tell me a bit about your child so I can share the best play ideas for you! 🎲✨

🏎️ Great! Let's go! 🏎️

Tap 'Let’s Play!' and I’ll share a simple, fun, and free activity you can do together!
Let’s Play!
What should we do next?
Another fun idea, please!
Let's try an activity for a different age!
Perfect! 🌟
Learn more tips to support my child
Change my language
Sure!
Stop for today
See you next time! You can message {PLAY} whenever you would like another easy and fun play idea.

I can do more than just play! 🎉 In this chat, you can also get ParentText.

ParentText can help you improve your relationship with your child in just 5 days—totally free!

Want to give it a try?
Yes
No
Great, let's do it!
That's okay. If you change your mind, you can always message {PLAY} if you want another activity or {START} if you want to start the programme.
Quick question for you! 🤔 What are the benefits of play?
Play is fun

Absolutely! Play is fun – and it also helps your child grow and supports both your mental health and your child’s.

Want to learn more? Complete the full survey here: {IOGT link}
Play supports mental health for both children and caregivers

Yes! Play can boost your mood and reduce stress – and it also encourages your child’s development in ways that are fun for you both.

Want to learn more? Complete the full survey here: {IOGT link}
Play promotes a child's overall development

That’s right! Play builds important life skills – and it also supports emotional wellbeing for both you and your child in a fun way.

Want to learn more? Complete the full survey here: {IOGT link}
All of the above

Exactly! Play is fun, it supports mental health, and it helps your child grow – all at the same time. Everyone wins!

Want to learn more? Complete the full survey here: {IOGT link}
